PHASE 1

Top 1/3 of Home Page
Text box: User can enter a phrase to be rephrased
Text box: User can describe the context; and how they need the phrase rephrased (funnier, more professional, etc.). Ideally the "how I need the phrase rephrased" piece would be a drop-down menu.
Submit button
--
Bottom 2/3 of Home Page
Clickable list of phrases submitted.
If a user clicks on an item in the list, she sees
- the context and request
- a text box where she can submit a suggestion
- a submit button
- a list of suggestions to date


PHASE 2

Home Page Sidebar:
Text box: username
Text box: password
Login button
Link to User Profile Page
Create account link
--
In this phase, when the user clicks "Submit" on the home page they should be taken to the "Submit and Share Page"
--
Submit and Share Page
Allows users to share their rephrase request w/friends via email, facebook, or twitter, in addition to publishing it on the site for public viewing.

After a user shares/submits, they should be directed back toward the home page.
--
User Profile Page
Display username
Display list of phrases submitted for rephrasing
Under a separate heading, display list of questions for which the user has offered answers
--
Create Account page
User can pick username, pw